<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-10T08:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-10T08:30:00-05:00" n="852" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">856B.00/23: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Curaçao</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Huddleston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curaçao</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-10T09:00:00-04:30">May
                                        10, 1940—9 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have been informed by the Colonial Secretary that martial law-was
                                declared in Curaçao this morning and that the German crews of the 7
                                German merchant vessels in port numbering about 350 persons are
                                being held in the Emma school here. German Austrian residents
                                approximating 50 people have also been arrested, all of these
                                individuals will be interned at Bonaire Island. Sand bags are being
                                placed over local recently constructed steel air raid shelters.
                                Banks are not quoting foreign exchange rates today.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Huddleston</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>